  {
    "name": "gRPC Services",
    "description": "Native gRPC calls.\n\nPRE-REQUISITES:\n1. Use Postman v10+ (gRPC is natively supported).\n2. For each request click 'New' → 'gRPC Request' (or open via the URL bar).\n3. In the URL field paste the server address shown per request.\n4. Click 'Select a method' → 'Import a .proto file' and import the relevant .proto from the project.\n5. Pick the method, paste the JSON body, then click 'Invoke'.\n\nAlt — grpcurl (CLI):\n  grpcurl -plaintext -d '{\"baseSalary\":95000}' localhost:15051 payroll.PayrollService/CalculateSalary",
    "item": [

      {
        "name": "Payroll gRPC — localhost:15051",
        "item": [
          {
            "name": "CalculateSalary",
            "request": {
              "method": "POST",
              "header": [],
              "body": {
                "mode": "raw",
                "raw": "{\n  \"baseSalary\": 95000\n}",
                "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
              },
              "url": {
                "raw": "grpc://{{grpc_payroll}}/payroll.PayrollService/CalculateSalary",
                "protocol": "grpc",
                "host": ["localhost"],
                "port": "15051",
                "path": ["payroll.PayrollService", "CalculateSalary"]
              },
              "description": "Proto: grpc-service/payroll.proto\nPackage: payroll\nService: PayrollService\n\nRequest fields:\n  baseSalary (double) — gross salary before tax\n\nResponse fields:\n  finalSalary, taxDeduction, taxRate\n\nCLI equivalent:\n  grpcurl -plaintext -d '{\"baseSalary\":95000}' localhost:15051 payroll.PayrollService/CalculateSalary"
            },
            "protocolProfileBehavior": { "disableBodyPruning": true },
            "response": []
          }
        ]
      },

